Brooklyn Union Gas Co said it hascontracted to purchase up to 60 mln cubic feet of natural gasper day from Shell Oil Co, a Royal Dutch/Shell Group &lt;RD> &lt;SC>subsidiary.    Brooklyn Union said the long-term contract will cover about15 pct of its total supplies.    A spokesman said Shell and the utility agreed to notdisclose the length of the contract or the price of the gas,which he described as competitive with a market sensitiveescalation formula.       Brooklyn Union said the gas from Shell Oil will replaceabout 25 pct of the gas previously supplied by Transco EnergyInc's &lt;E> Transcontinental Gas Pipe Line Corp subsidiary.    The utility said Transcontinental will transport the gasbeing purchased from Shell Oil, possibly beginning as soon asNovember 1. Reuter&#3;